# Patch 0030 — Kavacha top-right menu button + registry-driven panel
# (ROADMAP Phase 3 UX; discoverability).
#
# WHAT: a visible gear button (#kavacha-menu-button) prepended into the
# top-right toolbar cluster (#zen-sidebar-top-buttons) that opens an arrow
# panel (#kavacha-menu-panel) listing everything Kavacha can do. The panel is
# GENERATED FROM THE COMMAND REGISTRY (patch 0027): it iterates
# KavachaCommandDomainOrder and, per domain, emits KavachaCommandRegistry
# .getByDomain(domain) as rows under a localized domain header, skipping any
# command whose isAvailable(window) is false. A "Settings" row at the top opens
# about:preferences — the full settings surface. KavachaMenu.sys.mjs is a
# process singleton (init) with per-window UI (setupWindow); ZenStartup calls
# both per window, mirroring the layout/theme engines (ADR 0008).
#
# WHY: until now every Kavacha feature was reachable ONLY through the Cmd+K
# command palette — nothing surfaced them in the chrome, so a user who never
# learned the shortcut never discovered them. The panel closes that gap. Because
# it is generated from the registry rather than a hand-maintained list, it never
# drifts: features added later, and the marketplace's (patch 0028) / plugins'
# (patch 0029) runtime commands, appear automatically. It is rebuilt on every
# popupshowing so runtime-registered and availability-gated commands stay live.
# The quick-toggles (Theme switch, Tab layout, Density, New-tab style) are
# already APPEARANCE registry commands, so they surface in the generated list —
# no duplicate strip. This does NOT add a preferences pane (that is patch 0031)
# and does NOT edit KavachaCommandRegistry (it only READS it).
#
# NOT BUILD-VERIFIED: authored against the post-0029 tree without a build. Adds
# src/zen/common/sys/KavachaMenu.sys.mjs and
# src/zen/common/styles/kavacha-menu.inc.css; touches
# src/zen/common/modules/ZenStartup.mjs, src/zen/common/moz.build,
# src/zen/common/styles/zen-theme.css, and
# locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-command-palette.ftl. Run
# `git -C browser/zen-upstream apply --check` + a Marionette pass (click the
# gear, confirm the panel lists Settings then every domain section, invoke a
# command, confirm the panel gains a marketplace/plugin command at runtime)
# before marking the ROADMAP item verified. Applies on top of 0029.
diff --git a/locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-command-palette.ftl b/locales/en-US/browser/browser/zen-command-palette.ftl
